<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="idb9beb149-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Rules 37 and 39 of the Federal Rules of Criminal Procedure were abrogated <date date="1967-12-04">Dec. 4, 1967</date>, eff. <date date="1968-07-01">July 1, 1968</date>, and are covered by Rule 10, Federal Rules of Appellate Procedure, set out in the Appendix to Title 28, Judiciary and Judicial Procedure.</p>
